De Tomaso Industries Inc. said it increased its ownership stake in Officine Alfieri Maserati S.p.
A. to 84% from 51%. 

An Italian subsidiary of De Tomaso exercised a three-year-old option to buy the remaining shares of Maserati owned by the Italian government.
De Tomaso didn't disclose a price but said it would pay off the option exercise price in six annual payments beginning in September 1990. 

Chrysler Corp. owns the 16% of Maserati not owned by De Tomaso.
Maserati makes about 3,500 luxury cars a year. 

